# Subagent Routing

Use these routing rules for all GrooveGraph Next work.

## 1. Default hierarchy

- `GPT-5.4` stays at the top as orchestrator.
- `Composer 1.5` handles Cursor-native meta work.
- `GPT-5.4-mini` handles research, review, testing analysis, and graphics direction.
- `GPT-5.4-nano` handles triage, compression, and routing.
- `GPT-5.3-codex` handles bounded implementation.

## 2. Route by work type

- rules, prompts, skills, and tool contracts -> `composer-meta`
- exploration -> `explorer`
- bounded code work -> `implementer`
- review -> `reviewer`
- workflow validation -> `tester`
- cleanup analysis and removal proposals -> `hygienist`
- graphics and visual briefs -> `graphic-artist`
- Azure baseline, deployment, and preservation work -> `infrastructure-deployment`

## 2a. Agent to model assignment

- `orchestrator` -> `GPT-5.4`
- `composer-meta` -> `Composer 1.5`
- `explorer` -> `GPT-5.4-mini`
- `implementer` -> `GPT-5.3-codex`
- `reviewer` -> `GPT-5.4-mini`
- `tester` -> `GPT-5.4-mini`
- `hygienist` -> `GPT-5.4-nano`
- `graphic-artist` -> `GPT-5.4-mini`
- `infrastructure-deployment` -> `GPT-5.4-mini`

## 3. Escalation

Escalate to the orchestrator when:

- multiple outputs conflict
- scope changes materially
- the user needs a cross-domain synthesis
